cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.CR. 

The paper is about a project for collecting and storing bugs for automatic program repair studies in Java. It discusses the approach employed by the project and the bugs collected. The paper is likely to belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category as it deals with software testing and bug fixing. It may also belong to Programming Languages (cs.PL) as it discusses the use of Java and the creation of branches with bugs in a given GitHub repository. The paper may also be relevant to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category as it deals with the execution of test suites and the reproduction of bugs. It may also be relevant to the Learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it discusses the use of Continuous Integration (CI) to identify buggy and patched program version candidates. Finally, it may be relevant to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category as it discusses the public availability and extensibility of the bug benchmark.
